1
00:00:05,260 --> 00:00:07,875
Kṛṣṇa consciousness came from
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur,

2
00:00:07,875 --> 00:00:09,814
to Saraswatī Ṭhākur, to his followers.

3
00:00:09,814 --> 00:00:12,138
[Divine Compensation]

4
00:00:12,138 --> 00:00:17,826
So you see the expansion, an extension
of the Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement.

5
00:00:17,826 --> 00:00:20,145
I’ve thought about this
for a long time.

6
00:00:20,145 --> 00:00:22,826
Like, as you implied, 
so many devotees

7
00:00:22,826 --> 00:00:27,656
—and I knew them, you know,
I mean they know me too—

8
00:00:27,656 --> 00:00:32,464
we’d think, “How did this happen
with this group?”

9
00:00:32,464 --> 00:00:37,226
Knowing what our flaws are,
lack of qualifications, etc.

10
00:00:37,226 --> 00:00:41,176
It reminds me of what one of my friends
said about Sureśvāri’s husband,

11
00:00:41,176 --> 00:00:45,177
Vṛṣākapi Prabhu, who’s
a very dear friend of mine,

12
00:00:45,177 --> 00:00:51,009
when he joined some temple
in a city in America,

13
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:54,144
and her husband was 
the temple president,

14
00:00:54,144 --> 00:00:59,055
he said, “I thought I’d met
the most advanced spiritual person,

15
00:00:59,055 --> 00:01:02,842
like, in the world, in the universe.”

16
00:01:02,842 --> 00:01:06,675
And later … I mean
we dearly love him,

17
00:01:06,675 --> 00:01:11,842
and he helped us with Guru Mahārāj,
preaching in the very beginning,

18
00:01:11,842 --> 00:01:16,225
but I could say, if he was here,
or if he’s watching us,

19
00:01:16,225 --> 00:01:19,984
his reputation was not such, later.

20
00:01:19,984 --> 00:01:22,057
But that devotee said,
“When I met him I thought

21
00:01:22,057 --> 00:01:24,926
he was the most spiritually
advanced person I ever met,

22
00:01:24,926 --> 00:01:26,933
like in the whole world
and the universe.”

23
00:01:26,933 --> 00:01:30,703
And I said, “You know what?
He was!

24
00:01:30,703 --> 00:01:35,116
He was the most spiritually advanced
person you ever met,

25
00:01:35,116 --> 00:01:37,746
in the whole universe.”

26
00:01:37,746 --> 00:01:41,545
And why there was some potency
to what he said

27
00:01:41,545 --> 00:01:47,677
is because Prabhupād was
the pure devotee leading that kīrtan.

28
00:01:47,677 --> 00:01:51,411
So all of his disciples,
whatever they were doing,

29
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:54,464
they were doing on his order.

30
00:01:54,464 --> 00:01:57,280
It goes back to Mahāprabhu;
Mahāprabhu is saying,

31
00:01:57,280 --> 00:02:01,169
āmāra ājñāya guru hañā
tāra’ ei deśa

32
00:02:01,169 --> 00:02:04,044
yāre dekha, tāre kaha
‘kṛṣṇa’-upadeśa (Cc: Madhya, 2.7.128),

33
00:02:04,044 --> 00:02:07,426
“On my order, I’m telling you,

34
00:02:07,426 --> 00:02:10,008
Kṛṣṇa Upadeśa, you tell everyone

35
00:02:10,008 --> 00:02:12,304
Kṛṣṇa's ins[tructions]."
It’s Mahāprabhu’s order!

36
00:02:12,304 --> 00:02:15,119
And then Chaitanya Saraswat:
from Mahāprabhu

37
00:02:15,119 --> 00:02:18,168
to Saraswatī Ṭhākur and his followers.

38
00:02:18,168 --> 00:02:25,464
Guru Mahārāj’s explanation of why
Chaitanya Saraswat Math; one explanation.

39
00:02:25,464 --> 00:02:29,745
So Mahāprabhu’s divine order
and sanction in the background,

40
00:02:29,745 --> 00:02:33,627
then, Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur

41
00:02:34,842 --> 00:02:38,926
resetting the course;
they needed a reset.

42
00:02:38,926 --> 00:02:41,152
Like we had to do a reset

43
00:02:41,152 --> 00:02:46,342
when things got really out of hand

44
00:02:46,342 --> 00:02:48,465
and off-track in time,

45
00:02:48,465 --> 00:02:54,259
Bhakti Vinoda Ṭhākur reset
the Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement.

46
00:02:54,259 --> 00:02:57,384
So then to Saraswatī Ṭhākur
and his followers.

47
00:02:57,384 --> 00:03:04,385
So Prabhupād is actually infusing
the kīrtan of his disciples with potency,

48
00:03:04,385 --> 00:03:11,834
and compensating; Kṛṣṇa’s compensating
for their lack of qualification.

49
00:03:11,834 --> 00:03:16,904
So we saw, mysteriously,
how potent this movement was,

50
00:03:16,904 --> 00:03:19,065
even if sometimes the devotees

51
00:03:19,065 --> 00:03:21,754
—just for the sake of argument—
let’s say,

52
00:03:21,754 --> 00:03:24,705
misrepresented something;

53
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:29,006
maybe conceptually something was
not perfectly represented,

54
00:03:29,006 --> 00:03:30,676
and Kṛṣṇa wanted to say, “No,

55
00:03:30,676 --> 00:03:39,009
I personally compensate for any
deficiencies that my devotees have.”

56
00:03:39,009 --> 00:03:44,762
So the reason I mentioned this
is because, through …

57
00:03:44,784 --> 00:03:48,065
here I’m not saying about Prabhupād,
Guru Mahārāj, Gurudev,

58
00:03:48,065 --> 00:03:50,676
I’m talking about the devotees

59
00:03:50,676 --> 00:03:56,544
who were instrumental in spreading
Kṛṣṇa consciousness all over the world,

60
00:03:56,544 --> 00:03:59,385
with all their flaws and deficiencies,

61
00:03:59,385 --> 00:04:02,288
Kṛṣṇa compensated it all

62
00:04:02,288 --> 00:04:06,985
so people would have
some divine transaction.

63
00:04:06,985 --> 00:04:09,464
Even if they didn’t 100% get it right,

64
00:04:09,464 --> 00:04:11,953
the person was affected.

65
00:04:11,953 --> 00:04:14,182
In their heart they got something.

66
00:04:14,182 --> 00:04:16,994
So all this Harinam,
the Nagar-saṇkīrtan,

67
00:04:16,994 --> 00:04:19,384
the many things
the devotees did,

68
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:22,783
the people on the other side,
they do get something,

69
00:04:22,783 --> 00:04:25,426
and it’s real.

70
00:04:25,426 --> 00:04:27,509
And if there’s some fault 
on our part,

71
00:04:27,509 --> 00:04:30,624
Kṛṣṇa’s compensating for that.

72
00:04:30,624 --> 00:04:33,064
That’s why I’m saying this.

73
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:38,386
So how does this translate on down,

74
00:04:38,386 --> 00:04:40,591
from the pure devotees
who are leading,

75
00:04:40,591 --> 00:04:44,009
to their surrogates 
and representatives?

76
00:04:44,009 --> 00:04:49,259
Then we want the devotees
who are leading those kīrtans,

77
00:04:49,259 --> 00:04:52,424
that they’re, you know,
devotees in good standing,

78
00:04:52,424 --> 00:04:54,508
they’re initiated devotees.

79
00:04:54,508 --> 00:04:57,931
They will lead the kīrtans.

